              .productDetail__detail-left
                h2.productDetail__contentAttributes
                  p Bora Bora White Sand is a natural exfoliant from lagoons of polynesian high islands. The Polynesian archipelagos were formed millions of years ago with the emergence of volcanos. As soon as the volcanic activity was finished, coral started developing along the coast, rich is diverse trace elements. The natural process of erosoin leads to the coral detaching itself and creating small particles that arrive on the shore creating white sand beaches. Once picked, the sand is crushed and a natural exfoliating ingredient, Bora Bora White Sand, is formed.
                  p Bora Bora White Sand consists of fine particles (<500um) of coral that have washed ashore on the beaches of Polynesia. Bora Bora White Sand is crushed and riddled in order to obtain a powder. Bora Bora White Sand has natural mineral exfoliation and works best on the face and body in exfoliating gels and exfoliating emulsions.
                  p Bora Bora White Sand is a white to ivory find powder with a neutral odor. Bora Bora White Sand is insoluble in oil and water.  
